## Feature: Application Logs Viewer in Settings (Admin)

### Context
Administrators wanted a way to read the OntoBricks application logs directly in the UI without leaving the Databricks Apps console. A new "Logs" section under Settings → Admin now streams a live tail of the rotating log file (`ontobricks.log`) with level filtering, text search, configurable line count, and auto-refresh.

### Changes

1. **`src/api/routers/internal/settings.py`** — Added `GET /settings/logs?lines=N` endpoint (admin-only via `require(ROLE_ADMIN)`). Uses `LogManager.instance()` to locate the log file path and reads the last *N* lines (default 200, max 5 000) asynchronously via `run_blocking`. Also added `LogManager` to the module import.

2. **`src/front/config/menu_config.json`** — Added `"logs"` item (`bi-terminal` icon) to the `settings-admin` group, `admin_only: true`.

3. **`src/front/templates/partials/settings/_settings_logs.html`** — New partial: toolbar with level-filter buttons (ALL / DEBUG / INFO / WARNING / ERROR), text-search input, line-count selector, auto-refresh toggle and manual Refresh button; a dark `<pre>`-based console panel; and a footer showing the log file path and current level.

4. **`src/front/static/config/js/settings-logs.js`** — New JS module: lazy-loads on `sidebarSectionChanged` with `section === "logs"`, fetches `/settings/logs`, parses text-format and JSON-format log lines, colour-codes by level, applies level and text filters, auto-scrolls to bottom, and starts a 10-second auto-refresh interval on first load.

5. **`src/front/templates/settings.html`** — Added `<div id="logs-section" …>` inside the `{% if user_role == 'admin' %}` block (includes the new partial) and the corresponding `<script>` tag for `settings-logs.js`.

### Modified Files
- `src/api/routers/internal/settings.py` — `GET /settings/logs` + `GET /settings/logs/download`
- `src/front/config/menu_config.json`
- `src/front/templates/partials/settings/_settings_logs.html` (new)
- `src/front/static/config/js/settings-logs.js` (new)
- `src/front/templates/settings.html` — Refresh / Auto-refresh / Download controls in section header
- `src/front/static/global/css/sidebar-layout.css` — logs section fills viewport (same pattern as sigmagraph)

### Test Results
- 2651 unit/integration tests passed, 57 skipped. Pre-existing `pyshacl not installed` failure unrelated.

