## fix: OWL export uses domain name as namespace prefix

### Context
When exporting an OWL file the default namespace was bound to the empty prefix (`@prefix : <...#>`), making the Turtle output harder to read. The domain name (lowercase, alphanumeric) is now used as the prefix so exports produce e.g. `@prefix mydomain: <https://databricks-ontology.com/MyDomain#> .`.

### Changes
1. `src/back/core/w3c/owl/OntologyGenerator.py` — derive a clean lowercase prefix from `ontology_name` (strip non-alphanumeric chars, lowercase); bind it instead of the empty string `""`.

### Modified files
- `src/back/core/w3c/owl/OntologyGenerator.py`

### Test Results
- 28 existing OWL generator / roundtrip unit tests pass.
